  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement node mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method. The supporting ValidationResult is, however, generated by a numerical-simulation activity. The narrative characterises the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to bench testing, but the structured activityType field disagrees with requiredVerificationMethod, instantiating weakener W-AR-03.",
